<br>
 A lawyer in the Chicago/suburb area approaches the city attorney before court starts and they BS a little.<br>
<br>
 Then the city attorney asks the cop was this guy a jagoff or was he polite? If the cop says he was ok then when the clerk calls the ticket up and the judge asks you how you plea, your attorney says guilty and the city attorney who he spoke with steps up and says judge we recommend supervision. So long as your driving record is not really bad the judge fines ya 65 to 95 bucks and your out with no ticket on your record.<br>
<br>
Now with no attorney to BS with the city attorney what happens is the clerk calls you up you say guilty the judge either gives you a convicition or if you record is good you get traffic safety school (4hr school 1st time, 8hr school 2nd time) with a fine.<br>
<br>
Occasionally with no attorney and a guilty plea you get just what I first mentioned with attorney but thats rare.<br>
<br>
 With no attorney and a not guilty plea if the cop is there less than 1 out of 100 are found not guilty.<br>
<br>
Soooooo if your guilty and you want no safety school or conviction get an attorney. Oh and to those who try and talk to the city attorney without using a lawyer...forget it. Its like some secret attorney club...if you dont know the secret handshake they wont even talk to you heh heh.<br>
<br>
Callabran Steelshark<br>
Warlord<br>
